-- Air France Open to Air Berlin Cooperation, FT Deutschland Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-03-09T03:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-09/air-france-open-to-air-berlin-cooperation-ft-deutschland-says.html
Air France-KLM (AF)  Group is open to
involving  Air Berlin Plc (AB1)  in a potential partnership with  Etihad
Airways , Financial Times Deutschland cited Jean-Cyril Spinetta,
Air France-KLM’s chief executive officer, as saying.  While Air Berlin hasn’t approached Air France-KLM,
codeshare flights could be part of an agreement the carrier is
discussing with  Air Berlin shareholder  Etihad, the newspaper
cited Spinetta as saying in an interview at a press conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
